-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Intended Use and Media Rights
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

MusicHat is a stream interaction and queue management application. Its primary
designed function is enabling live-stream audiences to participate in a
moderated song queue and to display audio visualizations during live
presentations. The application uses the yt-dlp library as a technical
transport layer to resolve and access audio streams at URLs supplied by end
users.

This software does not grant, imply, or substitute for any copyright license,
public performance right, synchronization right, or other intellectual
property right in the media content accessed through it. Copyright in musical
works, sound recordings, and audiovisual content belongs to the respective
rights holders and is unaffected by use of this software.

Public performance of copyrighted music — including in live streams — typically
requires a license from the applicable performing rights organization in your
jurisdiction (such as ASCAP, BMI, SESAC, SOCAN, PRS for Music, APRA AMCOS, or
equivalent bodies). Users of this application are expected to have obtained all
necessary rights and licenses for any music they present publicly through it
before doing so.

The ability to resolve and access audio streams is incidental to the
application's core purpose of audience interaction, queue moderation, and
visualization. This application is not designed or intended as a substitute for
a licensed music distribution or streaming service.
